In 2019, the band covered the New Order albums Technique and Republic while touring the UK and North America. On 5 July 2019, the band performed an orchestral rendition of Joy Division songs with the Manchester Camerata at the Royal Albert Hall. Guest vocalists included Natalie Findlay, Mica Miller and Bastien Marshall. In August, they worked with The Metropolitan Orchestra to perform the set in Australia.

Forgotten Pleasures is the debut studio album release by Findlay. It was released on March 3, 2017 via digital, cd, limited vinyl under BMG.  Findlay is accompanied by Jules Apollinaire (also a co-producer) on keyboards, bass and guitar. Ben Simon on guitar, Christina Lamas on drums, as well as producers Jake Gosling (The Libertines, Ed Sheeran), Samy Osta (Woman, Fire Chatterton, Rover!) and Flood (Nick Cave, Depeche Mode, Smashing Pumpkins).

Ttrruuces (stylized in all caps) is an English psychedelic rock band, formed by Jules Apollinaire and Natalie Findlay in 2019. The band was based in London but then relocated to France for a year to fully immerse themselves in creating their debut album.
Jules Apollinaire and Natalie Findlay first met in the summer of 2014. As they both lived on Broadway Market in East London, they started to hung out to later realize how alike they were.
